# Design Rules — Non-Negotiable

## Identity

This is a luxury boudoir photography website. Every pixel must serve the photograph. If a design decision does not make the images feel more powerful, it is wrong.

## Forbidden Patterns

These patterns are **banned**. If you catch yourself building any of these, stop and redesign.

### Layout
- No centered hero sections with a headline + subheadline + CTA button
- No 3-column feature grids (icon + title + description)
- No card carousels or sliders
- No testimonial rotators
- No pricing tables
- No "About Us" sections with circular photos in a grid
- No symmetrical 50/50 split sections
- No uniform card grids (same size, same spacing)
- No sticky CTA bars or floating action buttons

### Typography
- No headlines larger than `clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem)` — let spacing do the work
- No bold body text — light and regular weights only
- No centered paragraphs longer than 2 lines
- No ALL CAPS for anything longer than 3 words
- No decorative fonts beyond the brand serif

### Color
- No saturated colors anywhere on the page
- No colored backgrounds (only near-black tones)
- No colored text (only off-white and muted accent)
- No gradients as decoration
- No colored buttons — text links with underlines only

### Animation
- No bounce easing
- No elastic overshoot
- No continuous loops
- No scale transforms above 1.05
- No blur/filter transitions in animations
- No more than 2 animated elements visible at once
- No animation on page load — wait 200ms minimum
- No hover animations on mobile (no hover state exists)

### Images
- No rounded corners on photographs
- No drop shadows on photographs
- No image borders or frames
- No square crops unless the photographer intended it
- No image zoom on hover (distorts composition)
- No watermarks in the UI layer

## Required Patterns

### Layout
- Asymmetric compositions — image dominant, text supporting
- Edge-to-edge images on mobile
- Generous vertical spacing between sections (`clamp(4rem, 10vh, 8rem)`)
- Text width capped at `52ch` maximum
- Broken grid on desktop — images can overlap text zones
- Each "screen" (100vh) should contain one idea maximum

### Typography
- Brand serif for display, sans-serif for body
- Letter-spacing as a design tool — `0.08em` to `0.2em` for labels
- Fluid type with `clamp()` — no fixed px sizes
- Hierarchy through weight and spacing, not size

### Color
- Warm near-black backgrounds (#0a0908 range)
- Warm off-white text (#F0EBE3 range)
- One metallic accent (champagne #C4A88A) used sparingly
- Section tone variations for rhythm (near-black variants)

### Images
- Default: desaturated (grayscale 80% + slight contrast boost)
- Hover/active: full color with 600ms transition
- Next.js `<Image>` with proper `sizes` attribute always
- Blur-up placeholder for loading, never skeleton or spinner

### Animation
- anime.js for JS-triggered animations
- CSS transitions for hover/state changes
- IntersectionObserver for scroll triggers
- Transform-only: translate, scale, opacity
- Default easing: cubicBezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)
- Default duration: 800ms–1200ms
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Quality Gate

Before shipping any component, ask:

1. Does this feel like a photography exhibition or a website template?
2. Would this look right printed on matte black paper?
3. Is the photograph the dominant element?
4. Is there enough empty space?
5. Would removing this element make the page better?

If the answer to #5 is "yes" — remove it.